# Protei_Bulk Logs Directory

This directory contains all application logs generated by Protei_Bulk.

## Log Files:
- system.log: Main system operations and events
- debug.log: Detailed debugging information
- error.log: Error messages and stack traces
- startup.log: Application startup and initialization logs
- archive/: Rotated historical logs

## Log Levels:
- DEBUG: Detailed diagnostic information
- INFO: General informational messages
- WARNING: Warning messages for potential issues
- ERROR: Error messages for failures
- CRITICAL: Critical errors requiring immediate attention

## Log Rotation:
Logs are automatically rotated based on configuration in config/log.conf:
- By size: When log file reaches maximum size
- By time: Daily, weekly, or monthly rotation
- Rotated files are compressed and moved to archive/

## File Naming Convention:
- Active logs: <name>.log
- Rotated logs: <name>.log.1, <name>.log.2, etc.
- Compressed: <name>.log.YYYYMMDD.gz

## Monitoring:
- Real-time monitoring: tail -f system.log
- Error tracking: tail -f error.log
- Search logs: grep "pattern" *.log
- View compressed: zcat archive/system.log.20250116.gz | less

## Disk Space Management:
- Monitor disk usage regularly
- Configure appropriate retention policies
- Use log rotation to prevent disk space issues
- Archive old logs to external storage if needed

## Important:
- Do not manually delete active log files
- Ensure proper permissions for log directory
- Regular log analysis recommended for troubleshooting
